column1: #Text=—On Saturday week the members of the Gorky Friendly Society met at their clubhouse (Mr.

#Text=Thomas Hayters) to celebrate the jubilee of the society, and then moved in procession, beaded by the lbsley brass band and a prettily painted banner, on which was inscribed the words, " Jubilee of the Gorley Friendly Society, instituted July 21st, IMO," and their u4tial colours, in excellent order round the village.
#Text=On returning they were met by the children of the Ibsley church school, carrying numerous banners, who followed them to Gorley Green.
#Text=At the club-room a cold, but good and substantial, dinner was prepared for them, with plenty of good home brewed ale, which appeared to be heartily enjoyed.
#Text=Songs and toasts followed the removal of the cloth, and were kept up during the day.
#Text=On the green a boo,li and (Aber staudings were erected, where dancing commenced at sic p.m.
#Text=The children partook of tea and coke in a field close by.
#Text=Boson had provided in the green iu front of the house plenty of cake and good tea, to which upwrels of SOO men, women, and children sat down.
#Text=Ow whole went off with great satisfaction, and will be lung remembered by all who were present.
